  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of international, national, and institutional regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting obligations for financial institutions\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Creating mechanisms for asset seizure and recovery\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- Asset forfeiture\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement compliance programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Internal monitoring systems\n- Employee training on detecting suspicious transactions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
